        PA_CQ --> PA_LV
    end

    subgraph PB["PATH B — Semantic Detection · Three-Tier Cost Funnel"]
        direction TB

        subgraph T1["Tier 1 — Surface Selection · deterministic"]
            direction TB
            PB_HT["<b><i><u>Heuristic Targeting</u></i></b>\nQueries Joern CPG for language-agnostic surface selection\nCPG-based targeting: external-input nodes · auth-boundary nodes · AI agent config file nodes\nNo per-language rules required — CPG normalizes all languages to shared graph schema\nAI agent config files: MCP configs · instruction files · tool call response strings\nFile-level filtering — ~95% of files eliminated · zero LLM cost"]
            PB_CG["<b><i><u>Call Graph + CVE Enrichment + Resource ID Dataflow</u></i></b>\nCall graph extracted from Joern CPG — no separate build step required\nCVE enrichment: Trivy (Go library · Apache 2.0 · OSV + NVD + GitHub Advisory databases)\nExact CVE match → auto-flag · skip all further analysis\nZero-trust resource ID tracking: all external IDs treated as untrustworthy until\nexplicit authorization confirmed at each function boundary (BOLAZ formal model · 35 new CVEs)\nFlags IDOR/BOLA violations before classifier · zero LLM cost\nNo CVE match → heuristic fallback (dangerous functions · unsafe sinks)"]
        end

        subgraph T2["Tier 2 — Classifier Gate · semi-deterministic"]
            direction TB
            PB_CC["<b><i><u>Code Vulnerability Classifier</u></i></b>\nUniXcoder-Base-Nine · ~125M params · F1=94.73% on BigVul\nRuns locally on CPU · milliseconds per function · zero API cost\nSupported languages: Python · Java · JavaScript/TypeScript · Go · Ruby · PHP\nUnsupported languages (Rust · Kotlin · Swift · C#) → routed directly to LLM · classifier skipped\nHigh confidence vulnerable → flag directly · skip LLM\nHigh confidence safe → dismiss · skip LLM\nUncertain → escalate to Tier 2.5 (~15–25% of surfaces reach LLM)"]
            PB_CCCA["<b><i><u>Call Chain Context Assembler</u></i></b>\nFor each uncertain surface: traces call chain up to depth 3 from Joern CPG\nAssembles multi-function context: caller → surface → callee\nEnables multi-hop reasoning for vulnerabilities spanning multiple functions\nRequired for: IDOR · missing auth guards · middleware bypass · business logic flaws\nSingle-function context misses authorization flaw classes (JitVul / ACL 2025)"]
            PB_SFS["<b><i><u>Semantic Function Summarizer</u></i></b>\nTransforms assembled call chain context into function-level semantic abstractions\nEach function described as: what it does with untrusted data · sanitizers applied · sinks reached\nLLM never sees raw code — only semantic summaries · aligns with IRIS ICLR 2025 design\nReduces token footprint while preserving security-relevant semantics\nSeparate summary schemas per vulnerability class: taint-flow · auth-guard · logic-flaw"]
        end

        subgraph T3["Tier 3 — LLM Reasoning · targeted"]
            direction TB
            PB_TB["<b><i><u>Token Budget Controller</u></i></b>\nHard cap enforced per scan · UCCI-style uncertainty calibration\nRanks uncertain surfaces by CVE score × classifier uncertainty\nCFG-based chunking: function boundary + taint-critical sub-paths\nVulnerable code positioned at prompt start · mitigates lost-in-middle\nCompression applied only to non-security-critical context (boilerplate · import blocks)\nSecurity-critical lines (data sources · sanitizers · sinks) preserved uncompressed\nIntelligent surface selection preferred over compression · drops only after selection exhausted\nSensitivity filter: credentials and PII routed to secure model only"]
            PB_LS["<b><i><u>LLM Semantic Scan · Bounded ReAct Loop</u></i></b>\nReads only uncertain high-priority surfaces as semantic summaries — never raw code\nNever sees Tier 1 or Tier 2 dismissed surfaces · Never sees Path A results\nReAct loop (max 3 steps per surface): Thought → context request → Observation → verdict\nContext requests: additional call chain depth · CVE DB lookup · Scan Security Context Store\nProgressive constraint modeling: enumerates program state constraints before vulnerability verdict\nGrammar-constrained decoding: XGrammar enforces JSON schema at generation time\nChain-of-Draft reasoning: verbose CoT compressed to ~7.6% of tokens at same accuracy\nApproach 3 evolution: single scan becomes 3-agent ensemble — Reconnaissance → Exploitation → Verification"]
        end

